The paper proposes a new algorithm for color transfer between images, which involves using neural representations for matching and optimizing a local linear model for color transfer satisfying both local and global constraints. These techniques are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) research. The paper also mentions the use of a coarse-to-fine strategy, which is a common approach in multimedia (cs.MM) research. Additionally, the paper involves optimizing a model, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research.
